laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 12 mm, with surrounding fat stranding. There is inflammatory change extending to the base of the cecum. No evidence of extraluminal air or fluid collection. Hazy misty appearance in the mesentery with small mesenteric lymph nodes, most consistent with mesenteric panniculitis.
